# GitHub Actions

> Full registry: `docs/CURSOR_HANDOVER.md` §5. Path-scoped: `.github/instructions/github-actions.instructions.md`.

Workflows under `.github/workflows/` ship to production. **`post_gold.yml` runs hourly** and posts to `@GoldTickerLive` on X — breakage is public within the hour. Dry-run via `workflow_dispatch` before changing posting logic.

## Rules

- **Do not break existing cron schedules** — document human-readable cadence in a comment next to each `schedule` cron (UTC).
- **Do not modify goldpricez API fetch logic** without explicit owner instruction. Production fetch path is the provider-adapter chain in `gold-price-fetch.yml` (single production provider-call path; `post_gold.yml` reads committed `data/gold_price.json`).
- **Never trigger price-fetch / poster workflows on `push`** — schedule and `workflow_dispatch` only.
- All production workflows with side effects should support **`workflow_dispatch`** with `dry_run` where applicable.
- Declare `permissions:` explicitly (least privilege).
- Never log secrets; `${{ github.event.inputs.dry_run }}` is a **string** (`"true"` / `"false"`).

## `GOLD_PROVIDER_ORDER` (production chain)

Set in `gold-price-fetch.yml` and `post_gold.yml`:

```text
gold_api_com,twelvedata_xauusd,fmp_gcusd
```

Default in `.env.example` (local / broader adapter list):

```text
metal_sentinel,finnhub_oanda,fmp_gcusd,goldapi_io,twelvedata_xauusd,goldpricez
```

Do not switch the production provider in the same PR that adds it — separate PR after bakeoff (`gold-provider-bakeoff.yml`).

